(
Figs. 4–7
)

Head
. Light blue except post frons, vertex, and occiput, which are black and finely sculptured, which makes them iridescent (
Fig. 7c
), with two light brown diagonal light brown dashes lateral to the ocelli (
Figs. 5a–b
). Labium and genae greenish blue. Frons angulated. When alive eyes blue with ventral portion green (
Figs. 7a–c
). Rear of head black.

Thorax.
Black except middorsal stripe finely sculptured making it iridescent and light blue anterior lobe of prothorax, lateral sides of medium lobe of prothorax, triangular spots on anterior portion of mesepisternum, concave stripe on mesepimeron, metepisternum and metepimeron with a black notch above the posterior area of metapleural suture (
Figs. 7a–c
). Venter pale yellow and pruinescent. Lateral margin of posterior lobe of prothorax rounded (
Figs. 5a–b
). Legs: Coxae bluish grey; femora external surface black and inner surface grayish blue; tibia and tarsus light brown; spurs black. The spurs on femora increase in size from base to apex (seven in each metafemur), the spurs on tibiae decrease in size from base to apex (eight in each metatibia) (
Figs. 7a–c
).

Caudal appendages.
Cercus forcipate and almost as long as S10, in lateral view ventral side slightly concave, with a ventral tooth in its inner margin, directed inwards, which can be easily seen in dorsal view, ending in a rounded tip, with external surface black and with inner surface covered with white pruinescense (
Figs. 5e–h
); paraprocts small (0.3 of cercus) dorsally concave, dark brown (
Fig. 5e
).

Thorax.
Yellowish brown, except black middorsal stripe finely sculped and iridescent; anterior lobe of prothorax, concave stripe on posterior ¾ of mesepimeron, metepisternum, and metepimeron greenish gray (
Fig. 7b
); venter pale yellow. Posterior lobe of pronotum with medial lobe slightly bilobate, bearing a pair of medio-lateral elevated ridges (
Figs. 7c–d
). Mesostigmal plates smooth, with medial margins sclerotized, lateroapical portions raised with a black pit behind them (
Figs. 7c–d
). Abdominal venter pale yellow. Legs: Coxae light brown; femora external surface light brown and inner surface yellowish brown, apex black, tibiae and tarsus yellowish brown, and spurs black (
Fig. 7b
). The spurs on femora increase in size from base to apex (seven in left and eight in right femur), the spurs on tibiae decrease in size from base to apex (eight in both metatibia), tarsal claws well developed.

Abdomen.
Same pattern as males except green instead of blue and brown instead of black, also S8–9 brown and anterior margin of S9 and S10 blue (
Fig. 7b
). Cercus brown, semitriangular in lateral view, half as long as S10, triangular in dorsal view, almost in contact at base, gonapophyses finely serrulated, styli brown, as long as cerci (
Fig. 6b
).
